do Cadets often find themselves doing work in the classroom they never imagined they could do  Dedicated Faculty 96 percent of faculty hold Ph D s and are renowned for teaching excellence  mentorship  scholarly engagement  commitment to service  and encouragement of undergraduate research  Cadet study areas are adjacent to faculty offices  encouraging individual instruction and in depth communication  Academic Support Academic support services are designed to help cadets achieve their academic and professional goals  Services such as the Miller Academic Center  the Office for Academic Athletic Advising  the Math Education and Resource Center  and Career Services work together to help each cadet reach his or her full potential  Small Classes Small class sizes allow faculty to interact closely with cadets inside and outside the classroom  Distinguished Visitors Well known dignitaries  experts  and leaders regularly come to VMI to address the Corps of Cadets  offering diverse and stimulating perspectives on a wide range of topics  Center for Leadership and Ethics VMI s Center for Leadership and Ethics enhances the cadet experience by offering a range of opportunities for academic and character development  Cadets participating in the center s programs discuss leadership challenges  meet authors  and interact with distinguished leaders  Focus on Learning Many cadets point to the absence of ordinary college distractions and the presence of personal accountability as guideposts for their success Dedicated Faculty 96 percent of faculty hold Ph D s and are renowned for teaching excellence  mentorship  scholarly engagement  commitment to service  and encouragement of undergraduate research  Cadet study areas are adjacent to faculty offices  encouraging individual instruction and in depth communication  Academic Support Academic support services are designed to help cadets achieve their academic and professional goals  Services such as the Miller Academic Center  the Office f